{
	"name": "Ashen Remembrance",
	"type": "feature",
	"img": "icons/magic/fire/flame-burning-hand-purple.webp",
	"system": {
		"description": "<p>At 1st level, when you reduce a creature to 0 hit points or witness a creature die within 30 feet, you can use your reaction to absorb a fragment of its essence. Until the end of your next turn, you gain advantage on one attack roll, ability check, or saving throw of your choice. Alternatively, you can choose to absorb some of the knowledge of the deceased creature, giving you one of its skill or tool proficiencies until your next long rest.</p><p>You can use this feature a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, regaining all expended uses when you finish a long rest.</p>",
